## Configured-Impact Trace

Configured-Impact Trace:
- Scope mode: <<scope_mode|deployed/configured|static-source-only | deployed/configured | mixed-scope>>
- Configuration precondition: <<config_precondition|<describe config required>|how the vulnerable path is enabled in the in-scope environment - source config, runtime registration, deployment config, registry mapping, contract constructor, admin-set value, or live state for deployed/mixed-scope bounties>>
- Evidence: <<config_evidence_fileline|<file:line>|file:line / config-file / registration-site / live-state citation backing the configuration precondition>>
- Downstream consumer: <<downstream_consumer|<configured consumer name>|the exact configured downstream component that consumes the bad state/value/root/message and turns it into the claimed impact>>
- Hop-by-hop impact trace: <<hop_trace|<hop1 -> hop2 -> impact>|each hop bad-state -> ... -> impact, with a file:line / source citation or executed-PoC assertion per hop>>
- Executed in PoC? <<executed_in_poc|yes|yes | no>>
- If no, narrowed claim / severity cap: <<narrowed_claim|N/A - executed end-to-end|if the PoC executes only the upstream acceptance step and the downstream fund/message path is not executed-or-fully-source-traced, word the impact as "accepted forged/unfinalized state" / "state-integrity failure" and state the severity cap. E.g. "downstream fund-loss only if this client is configured for a value-bearing state machine; severity capped because that configuration is unproven".>>
- Triage-follow-up pre-answer:
  (a) Deployed/configured-chain assumption needed: <<triage_q_a|<assumption + citation>|name the exact deployed/configured-chain assumption the impact rests on, with the config/registration/live-state citation that backs it>>
  (b) Downstream runtime path that realizes impact: <<triage_q_b|<runtime path hop by hop>|name the executed or fully source-traced downstream runtime path that turns the accepted bad state into the claimed impact, hop by hop. A narrowed claim still has to answer both - narrowing changes the impact wording, not the two questions.>>

